    <h1> Social Urbanism
    </h1>
    <h2 id="main-header"> An urban development Policy and why social urbanism matters for sharing cities
    </h2>
    <h3> How Medellin has changed using Social Urbanism Policy?
    </h3>
      <p id="intro"> Learn more how Medellin use urban design, landscape architecture to reduce inequality and heal the environmental damage.
      </p>
 <figure>
     <img src="https://d36iur3orme9ke.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/12127893065_05d6f86d68_z.jpg" alt="Comunas de Medellin">
     <figcaption> Medellin and its slums  </figcaption>
     </figure>
 </body>
    <section>
      <h4> Welcome to Medellin </<h4>
        <p id="important-fact"> People expects to see drugs and poverty everywhere, too long ago you would been right.
    Medellin was a scary place with guns, gangs and drugs were making the city a place hard to live  but started to invest in its people and slums
        </p>
      <h5> How Medellin started to changed Positively?
      </h5>
      <p id= "paragraph1"> This Model was base on the "Barcelona Model" looking for a dialogue between architecture, infrastructure and planning.
  Requiered a highly urban, dense and compact planing, with a tight collaboration with politicians, planners and citizens.
      </p>
   <ul id="delivery">
       <li> Creating Safe Public Spaces like green parks and adding art monuments.
       </li>
       <li> Built moving staircases to go home up to the hills.
       </li>
       <li> Adding affordable and adapting cable railway to the most retired slums to connect them with strategic parts of
    the city and another slums nearby. Now, the population can travel half time going to downtown to improve
    their life opportinities.
       </li>
       <li>Adding Public Libraries where the access to education and techonology was a persisting gap.
       </li>
       <li> Providing training for jobs and job placement opportinities for the youngest population.
       </li>
      <li> The renovated Botanic garden to enjoy a family day, adding green landscape and a safety space to share with other without paying a fee.
      </li>
  </ul>
    <h5> Why is this important to share?
    </h5>
       <ol class="important-to-share">
  <li class="facts">Colombia has been  about more than 60 years in a internal war. </li>
  <li class="facts"> Internally there are more displaced people in Colombia than other country in the world</li>
  <li class="facts">Creation of a lot slums in the higher slopes </li>
  <li class="facts"> Unequaled city in stratification of socio economic classes.</li>
  <li class="facts"> Became in the most dangerous city in the world with over 381 homocides per 10.000 people </li>
      </ol>
